    "title": "Marzipan API",
    "version": "1.0.0",
    "description": "# Introduction\n\nThe Marzipan API is organized around REST. Our API has predictable resource-oriented URLs, accepts form-encoded request bodies, returns JSON-encoded responses, and uses standard HTTP response codes, authentication, and verbs.\n\n## Getting Started\n\nTo get started with the Marzipan API, you'll need to:\n\n1. **Register an account** using the `/account/register` endpoint\n2. **Login** to obtain authentication credentials\n3. **Explore** the available endpoints organized by category\n\n## Authentication\n\nAll API endpoints require authentication. Include your authentication token in the request headers.\n\n## Base URL\n\nAll API requests should be made to: `{{apiUrl}}`\n\n## Endpoints Overview\n\n- **Account**: User registration, login, and profile management\n- **Carts**: Shopping cart creation and management\n- **Products**: Product catalog and search functionality\n- **Subscriptions**: Subscription management and renewals\n- **CMS**: Content management system endpoints\n- **Search**: Global search functionality"
  },
